<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911220-0061</DOCNO><DOCID>911220-0061.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Degussa AG:   German Firm's Pretax Profit   Dropped 44% in Fiscal Year</HL><DATE>12/20/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   G.DGS</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)</MS><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)PRECIOUS METALS, STONES, GOLD, SILVER (PCS)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>EUROPE (EU)GERMANY (GE)WESTERN EUROPE (WEU)</RE><LP>   Degussa AG, a German chemicals concern, said group pretaxprofit plunged 44% for the fiscal year ended Sept. 30, on a4.1% drop in group sales.   Pretax profit dropped to 179 million marks ($114 million)from 318 million marks a year earlier. Group sales fell to13.35 billion marks from 13.92 billion marks.</LP><TEXT>   Degussa said the results, contained in a short &quot;overview,&quot;reflected &quot;an especially difficult year.&quot; An anticipatedimprovement in the second half of the year nevermaterialized.   The company announced a series of measures to cut costs.&quot;Some are already under way, others will follow,&quot; the companysaid. They include concentrating on the company's corebusinesses, reducing the number of production facilities,cutting fixed costs and increasing efficiency. The companywasn't more specific.</TEXT></DOC>